{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LRbYrax1oNhcxD7oB3q3ir","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: add-field\n     3→description: Add a new field to a Django model and propagate to admin, serializer, and factory. Use when adding model fields or database columns.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Add Field\n     7→\n     8→Add a field to a Django model and propagate it to admin, serializer, and factory.\n     9→\n    10→## Inputs\n    11→\n    12→Prefer structured arguments from `$ARGUMENTS` when available.\n    13→\n    14→Accepted forms:\n    15→\n    16→1. JSON object with keys:\n    17→   - `model_name`\n    18→   - `field_name`\n    19→   - `field_type`\n    20→   - `field_args`\n    21→   - `factory_default`\n    22→2. Positional args:\n    23→   - `<model_name> <field_name> <field_type> [field_args] [factory_default]`\n    24→\n    25→Normalization rules:\n    26→\n    27→- `field_args` should be raw Django field args without wrapping parentheses.\n    28→  Example: `max_length=20, default=\"bronze\"`\n    29→- `factory_default` should be a Python literal rendered into the factory line.\n    30→  For string defaults, include quotes in the value (example: `\"bronze\"`).\n    31→- If optional args are omitted, use:\n    32→  - `field_args: \"\"`\n    33→  - `factory_default: \"'test'\"`\n    34→\n    35→## Usage\n    36→\n    37→```bash\n    38→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\"model_name\": \"<Model>\", \"field_name\": \"<name>\", \"field_type\": \"<Type>\", \"field_args\": \"<args>\", \"factory_default\": \"<default>\"}'\n    39→```\n    40→\n    41→If invoked as `/add-field <model_name> <field_name> <field_type>`:\n    42→\n    43→```bash\n    44→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\"model_name\": \"$1\", \"field_name\": \"$2\", \"field_type\": \"$3\", \"field_args\": \"\", \"factory_default\": \"\\\"test\\\"\"}'\n    45→```\n    46→\n    47→## Variables\n    48→\n    49→- **model_name**: Model class name (e.g. `Reservation`)\n    50→- **field_name**: New field name (e.g. `loyalty_tier`)\n    51→- **field_type**: Django field type (e.g. `CharField`)\n    52→- **field_args**: Field arguments (e.g. `max_length=20, default=\"bronze\"`)\n    53→- **factory_default**: Factory default value (e.g. `\"bronze\"`)\n    54→\n    55→Extract these from the user's request.\n    56→\n    57→## Gotchas\n    58→\n    59→- If unsure about required variables, run:\n    60→  - `jig vars ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml`\n    61→- If jig exits non-zero, it prints rendered output to stderr. Use that output for one manual correction pass.\n    62→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f3d7b1da-3d16-413e-a91a-ec8b58ef12ab","uuid":"e080f64e-62c8-452a-b058-c692af32aecb"}
